"Kamal W.A.","Improving energy efficiency - The cost-effective way to mitigate global warming",1997,"Energy Conversion and Management","38","1",,"39","59",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0002631693&partnerID=40&md5=48e35b8b0adbe21cf71eb0641d17d5b2","College of Engineering, University of Qatar, Doha, Qatar","Kamal, W.A., College of Engineering, University of Qatar, Doha, Qatar","The growth in world population and in demand for energy worldwide, in particular in developing countries, is highlighted. The reflection on CO2 and other greenhouse gas emissions, and the subsequent effects on the shape of climatic changes, are examined. The paper then assesses the energy intensity of economies from different parts of the world, rich and poor, and demonstrates that significant savings in energy consumption can be made. Finally, the scope and means of achieving the expected improvements in energy efficiency in the different sectors of the economy (commercial and residential, industry and transportation) are discussed in detail. Examples of the energy saving technologies are presented. Copyright © 1996 Elsevier Science Ltd.","Energy conservation; Energy efficiency; Energy intensities of different economies; Global warming mitigation; Greenhouse effect",,,,,,,"Fourier, M., (1827) Mem Acad. Royal Sci. Inst. France, 7, p. 569; Arrhenius, S., (1896) Philadelphia Mag. J. Sci., 41, p. 237; Arrhenius, S., (1908) Worlds in the Making: The Evaluation of the Universe, , Harper, London; Walsh, M., (1990) Ann. Rev. Energy, 15, p. 217; Minzer, I., (1990) Ann. Rev. Energy, 15, p. 513; Schneider, S., (1989) Global Warming, Are We Entering the Greenhouse Century?, , Sierra Club Books, San Francisco; (1987) Current Issues in Atmospheric Change, , National Academy Press, Washington D.C; Cavanagh, R., (1989) Ann. Rev. Energy, 14, p. 353; Abrahamson, D., The changing atmosphere: Implications for global security (1989) The Challenge of Global Warming, p. 44. , 27 30 June 1988